-- Haemonetics to Buy Assets of Pall, Hemerus Medical
-- B y   T h e o   M u l l e n
-- 2012-04-29T17:28:16Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-04-29/haemonetics-to-buy-assets-of-pall-hemerus-medical-correct-.html
(Corrects to show two transactions.)  Haemonetics Corp. (HAE)  said it agreed to
acquire the blood collection and filtration assets of  Pall Corp. (PAL) 
for approximately $551 million, and separately agreed to buy
certain assets of Hemerus Medical LLC, a Minnesota-based company
that develops technologies for the collection of whole blood,
and processing and storage of blood components.  Haemonetics agreed to pay Pall $551 million, of which $536
million will be paid upon closing and the remaining $15 million
paid for additional assets to be delivered by 2016, the
statement said. Haemonetics said $475 million will be new
borrowings and $61 million will be from existing cash holdings.  Haemonetics did not disclose the purchase price for the
property of Hemerus.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Theo Mullen at 
 tmullen11@bloomberg.net  